Anybody out there making use of the `{% call() macro_name(args) %} {% endcall %}` blocks at all? Just reading through the jinja docs today and this def works in hubl. Essentially it is a way of calling a macro but youre able to pass the stuff inside of the call block through as a second macro ( kind of) In short youre passing a macro to a macro. But one of them is nameless. Seems like the main purpose is to prevent code duplication but im wondering how folks are using this if at all.

```{% macro dump_users(users) -%}
    &lt;ul&gt;
    {%- for user in users %}
        &lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;{{ user.username|e }}&lt;/p&gt;{{ caller(user) }}&lt;/li&gt;
    {%- endfor %}
    &lt;/ul&gt;
{%- endmacro %}

{% call(user) dump_users(list_of_user) %}
    &lt;dl&gt;
        &lt;dt&gt;Realname&lt;/dt&gt;
        &lt;dd&gt;{{ user.realname|e }}&lt;/dd&gt;
        &lt;dt&gt;Description&lt;/dt&gt;
        &lt;dd&gt;{{ user.description }}&lt;/dd&gt;
    &lt;/dl&gt;
{% endcall %}```
